Doctor Strange 2 SPOILER-FREE Review coming soon

#DoctorStrange was a weird (heh) movie experience. It was entertaining without ever really being good. And it failed to be good, despite all the individual elements being good. 

Story: amazing 
Acting: superb
Director: someone I like and respect. 

And yet… 1/9

The execution just flopped for me. 

It is objectively a better story than the first #DoctorStrange. Cumberbatch has become one of my favourite casting choices in the MCU. Xochitl Gomez is utterly utterly perfect. I want to see her in all the things forever. 2/9

Before digging in, the least believable moment in the whole movie is when Stephen wakes up from a nightmare beside a Surface Pro which somehow manages to stay upright. 

This is supposed to be a superhero horror comedy, not an exercise in total absurdism. #DoctorStrange

Spoiler free review of Doctor Strange and the Multiverse of Madness. 

TL;DR I’m not sure if I liked it yet, but I had a good time. 

#DoctorStrange

Some of the musical flourishes made my kids and I squeal. Especially the one where a certain bald character makes his MCU debut. 

I love Sam Raimi. I love superhero movies. I loved all the Raimi tropes and treasures on display and I loved the superheroics. #DoctorStrange 3/9

I just walked out of the movie feeling like the don’t belong together. 

Spider-Man 2 was a masterpiece. But the MCU has eclipsed that time and style of movie story telling and #DoctorStrange And the Multiverse of Madness highlights that I’m really unfortunate ways. 4/9

The dialog and performances, through Raimi’s direction just felt…off. The pacing in the first half of the movie felt rushed and like there was either a mandate to keep the running time to a cool two hours or Raimi just wanted to get to the Wil word stuff #DoctorStrange 5/9

All that said, I WAS entertained and you SHOULD see it. I laughed, I was appropriately fan serviced, my kids had jaw drop syndrome in places. I just couldn’t ever really immerse in the way I usually do with MCU movies. #DoctorStrange 7/9
